        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 2:14PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 214 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles east of J P Coleman State Park, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Riverton, Wright, Threet, and Waterloo.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 500 PM CDT for
northwestern Alabama.</instruction>
